Source: sysmaint
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Mohamed Elharery <Mohamed@Harery.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/Harery/SYSMAINT

Package: sysmaint
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4.2), apt, systemd, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: fwupd, snapd, dialog
Suggests: whiptail
Description: Multi-distro Linux maintenance with modern TUI (9 platforms)
 sysmaint is a multi-distro maintenance orchestrator supporting 9 platforms
 across 4 OS families: Debian (Ubuntu, Debian 13, Zorin), Red Hat (Fedora,
 CentOS, RHEL, Rocky, Alma), Arch (Arch, Manjaro), SUSE (openSUSE).
 .
 NEW in v2.5.0: Interactive TUI mode with modern 2026 UX/UI design.
 Features ANSI color gradients, animated ASCII art, card-based layouts,
 and multiple themes. Dual-boot CLI/TUI operation - use --gui flag.
 .
 Manages 6 package managers: APT, DNF, Pacman, Zypper, Snap, Flatpak.
 Features include disk cleanup, security audits, JSON telemetry, and
 unattended operation with systemd timer support.
